node.text: Remus the companion dog is a bit of a ball hog! 😹 See him and Kris the cheetah play on a nice summer day! This dynamic duo spends almost all of their time together- including sleepovers! Usually cheetahs stay with their dogs for around two years, but it all depends on the pair! 😻🐶⚽️

node.text: Happy #nationalzookeeperweek! The Cincinnati Zoo was voted the best Zoo in the country this year and that wouldn’t be possible without our amazing Zookeeper staff. The animal care teams devote their lives to conservation and the animals at the Cincinnati Zoo. Our keepers build trust and bonds with the animals in their care in order to provide the best care possible. So help us celebrate the zookeepers of the Cincinnati Zoo this week, and all year long! 🐾 💚 #weareaza

node.text: We're jumping for joy! Grab a friend and head to Hops, the Zoo’s craft beer garden that overlooks Roo Valley and features local breweries from Fifty West, High Grain, Karrikin Spirits, and MadTree. Sustainability is important. Hops is going for a 4-star rating from the Green Restaurant Association for Hops. Food operations will be disposable free, with real silverware and plates instead of single-use plastics. We’ll grow our own herbs, and source produce, cheeses and meats locally.

node.text: Happy #Caturday to Saddie the sand cat! The sand cat is equipped for desert life. Large ears radiate heat and covered with hair, its footpads are insulated from the hot sand. During extreme heat, they cool off in a burrow. They do not need to drink often as they get enough moisture from its prey!
